KwaZulu-Natal Premier, Sihle Zikalala, says there could be another hard lockdown if reckless behaviour continues. He's slammed the carefree attitude by some people in the province with many not bothering to wear masks and attending large gatherings. DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal Premier Sihle Zikalala warns of another hard lockdown if people continue to flout social distancing regulations. Zikalala says the government could be forced to implement hard lockdown during festive season, if reckless behaviour continues. He's slammed the carefree attitude by some people in the province with many not bothering to wear masks and attending large gatherings. READ: COVID-19: SA reports 53 deaths, 1,834 new infections The KZN Premier also warned alcohol sellers to toe the line and obey the law. Zikalala says some outlets are breaking the rules by trading during weekends. He says inspectors will be deployed to make sure the rules are adhered to. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.